My question for this week: Meta has announced plans to fully automate ad creation using AI by the end of 2026. These tools will enable businesses to generate complete ads‚Äîincluding images, videos, and text‚Äîbased on product images and marketing budgets, and offer precise targeting, such as geolocation-based customization. 
What are your thoughts on this development?
‚Ä¢    Could this democratize advertising for small businesses, or does it risk homogenizing creative content?
‚Ä¢    How might this impact traditional advertising agencies and creative professionals?
‚Ä¢    Are there ethical considerations in allowing AI to handle personalized ad targeting at scale?
